<!-- ABOUT SECTION -->
<section id="about" class="relative border-b border-line">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-8 py-20 sm:py-28">
    <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> About</span>
    <h2 class="mt-5 text-[2rem] sm:text-[2.6rem] leading-[1.05] font-bold">
      Built Alongside Real Service Businesses,<br class="hidden sm:block"/> Not in an Agency Bubble
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-7 space-y-5 text-text-soft text-[1.05rem] leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        I'm <span class="text-text font-medium">Bill</span> — the developer and strategist behind Designed to Elevate. I build alongside real service businesses, not from a generic agency template.
      </p>
      <p>
        The system started as a 378-vehicle quote wizard for <span class="text-text font-medium">Fitchin Automotive Detailing &amp; Window Tinting</span> in Coshocton, Ohio. It grew into a full platform — wizard, dashboard, scheduling, installer view, and customer follow-up flows — that's running live at the shop today.
      </p>
      <p>
        <span class="text-text font-medium">Modern Classic Barbershop &amp; Shave Parlor</span> in Zanesville helped shape the Square-integrated side of the work — premium custom design on top of Square's booking and payment APIs, with a custom waitlist, auto-review flow, and customer login layered on top.
      </p>
      <p>
        Designed to Elevate takes those same proven patterns and core platform pieces, then configures them around the next service business.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<!-- /ABOUT SECTION -->
